HEADWORD: Choriambus
<hw>Cho`ri*am"bus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Choriambi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Choriambuses</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>choriambus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ a
choreus + <?/ iambus.]</ety> <fld>(Anc. Pros.)</fld> <def>A foot
consisting of four syllables, of which the first and last are long, and
the other short (- ⟦cre⟧ ⟦cre⟧ -); that is, a choreus, or trochee, and
an iambus united.</def>⟦br⟧
